---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
---
<Base
  title="About — americawhat"
  description="What americawhat is: a curated running feed of absurd, deeply-American moments, and the wait, what ethos behind it."
  canonicalPath="/about/"
>
  <a href="/" class="back-link">&larr; back to feed</a>

  <header class="page-head">
    <div class="page-eyebrow">About</div>
    <h1 class="page-title">Wait, what.</h1>
  </header>

  <article class="page-card page-prose">
    <p>
      <strong>americawhat</strong> is a curated running feed of absurd, deeply-American
      moments — the news items, the police reports, the HOA memos, the fine print. The
      stuff that sounds made up and isn't. We collect the moments that make you stop,
      read it twice, and go <em>wait, what.</em>
    </p>
    <p>
      There's no thesis here, no hot take, no side. Just a steady drip of the strange
      and the everyday, filed under categories that shouldn't need to exist and somehow
      always do. If a story could only happen here, it belongs here.
    </p>
    <p>
      That's the whole idea. We collect them, source them, caption them, and get out of the way. You
      supply the double take.
    </p>
  </article>
</Base>
